No, the equipment does not become unequipped.  Equipment can be attached to creatures that are controlled by another player with cards like [autocard]Vulshok Battlemaster[/autocard].  The actual Equip ability can only target a creature you control, but once attached it doesn't care who controls what any more.

The important thing to note is that if you control the equipment, then you can pay the equip cost and move it to one of your creatures.  The person who controls the equipped creature can no longer pay the equip cost of the equipment, nor any other abilities of the equipment (such as [autocard]Sunforger[/autocard] or [autocard]Sword of the Paruns[/autocard]).  Equipment that grants abilities to the creature (such as [autocard]Viridian Longbow[/autocard]) are still only able to be activated by the controller of the creature, so read carefully!

